<TITLE> ACC to probe graft at private universities </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 26 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission will investigate alleged corruption and irregularities in private universities and has sought assistance from the University Grants Commission in the new move, an official said Thursday. "The ACC has gathered reports from the UGC," ACC director (administration) Col Hanif Iqbal told reporters in a press briefing. Replying to a question, Iqbal said: "Corruption and irregularities in public universities will also be investigatedin phases." The official also said special ACC teams had started investigation into irregularities in Viqarunnisa Noon School, Motijheel Ideal School and College, Titumir College, Sheikh Borhanuddin College and Lalmatia Girls College. The drive will go on, Iqbal said. The ACC is also investigating irregularities in the institutions with MPOs and the appointment of employees. Iqbal said the special teams of the ACC, connected with the education ministry, had collected "evidence" of irregularities about MPO in different schools and colleges. Replying to another question, Iqbal said the ACC would continue its work even if the National Coordination Committee for checking serious crimes did not exist. bdnew
